API - Application Programming Interface

Basic Component 

1 - baseURL - where your api server is hosted

2 - authentication (headers) - bearerToken, JWT, basic - username, password
        Content-Type 

3 - Method - GET (read or fetch) , POST (Create) , PUT (Update), PATCH (partial - update), DELETE (Delete)

4 - Endpoint (Service)

5 - Payload (Body) - Request-Body (JSON) , query param, path param 



6 - Response 
    a - Response Code - 200 - Success, 300 - Redirctional , 400 - Client , 500 - Server side
    b - Response body - detail of your Response
    c - Response Headers - header details of your response



